    "In addition to this, predictive analytics finds its application in precision farming, soil nutrients level estimation, predictions of crop yields, inventory management, and the facilitation of DSS (Kolipaka, 2020; Chandraprabha and Dhanaraj, 2021; Kumar et al., 2022).",
    "Mostly agricultural firms from developed countries are exploring this domain of AI for increased gains and better supply chain management.",
    "However, its direct use by the farmers is still in its nascent phase.",
    "Huge amounts of data, complicated data processing, and lack of training are a few of the prominent challenges of adopting predictive analytics in agriculture, particularly for developing nations.",
